#. <section class="sutta" id="sn52.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn52.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 52"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 52"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Rahogatavagga"
msgstr "1. In Private"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 9. Ambapālivanasutta → ambapālisuttaṃ (bj) | sabbaṃ or ambapāla (pts1)
msgctxt "sn52.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Ambapālivanasutta"
msgstr "9. In Ambapālī’s Wood"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.9:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca anuruddho āyasmā ca sāriputto vesāliyaṃ viharanti "
"ambapālivane."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerables Anuruddha and Sāriputta were staying near Vesālī, in "
"Ambapālī’s Wood."

msgctxt "sn52.9:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito … pe … "
"ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to "
"Anuruddha, and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.302"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.9:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Vippasannāni kho te, āvuso anuruddha, indriyāni, parisuddho mukhavaṇṇo "
"pariyodāto."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Anuruddha, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion "
"is pure and bright."

msgctxt "sn52.9:2.2"
msgid "Katamenāyasmā anuruddho vihārena etarahi bahulaṃ viharatī”ti?"
msgstr "What kind of meditation are you usually practicing these days?”"

msgctxt "sn52.9:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Catūsu khvāhaṃ, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto etarahi bahulaṃ "
"viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"“These days, reverend, I usually meditate with my mind firmly established in "
"the four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "sn52.9:2.4"
msgid "Katamesu catūsu?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn52.9:2.5"
msgid ""
"Idhāhaṃ, āvuso, kāye kāyānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr "I meditate observing an aspect of the body …"

msgctxt "sn52.9:2.6"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "feelings …"

msgctxt "sn52.9:2.7"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn52.9:2.8"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharāmi ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn52.9:2.9"
msgid ""
"imesu khvāhaṃ, āvuso, catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto etarahi "
"bahulaṃ viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"These days I usually meditate with my mind firmly established in these four "
"kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "sn52.9:2.10"
msgid ""
"Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro "
"anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, so imesu "
"catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacitto bahulaṃ viharatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed the "
"spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved "
"their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed "
"through enlightenment—usually meditates with their mind firmly established "
"in these four kinds of mindfulness meditation.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn52.9:3.1"
msgid "“Lābhā vata no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ vata no, āvuso."
msgstr "“We’re so fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate,"

msgctxt "sn52.9:3.2"
msgid ""
"Ye mayaṃ āyasmato anuruddhassa sammukhāva assumha āsabhiṃ vācaṃ "
"bhāsamānassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"to have heard such a dramatic statement in the presence of Venerable "
"Anuruddha.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.9:3.3"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
